"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [Amended by 1953 c.638 s.2;
1959 c.400 s.4; repealed by 1965 c.608 s.21]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.340</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [1965 c.535 s.1; 1975 c.278
s.3; 1991 c.144 s.2; repealed by 1993 c.45 s.170]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>TEACHER STANDARDS AND PRACTICES COMMISSION</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.350 Commission established;
confirmation; term; vacancy; effect of change in circumstances.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) There is
created a Teacher Standards and Practices Commission consisting of 17 members
appointed by the Governor subject to confirmation by the Senate in the manner
provided in ORS 171.562 and 171.565.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) The term of office of a member is three
years. Before the expiration of the term of a member, the Governor shall
appoint a successor to assume the duties on January 1 next following. A member
is eligible for reappointment but only for one additional term. In case of a
vacancy for any cause, the Governor shall make an appointment to become
immediately effective for the unexpired term.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (3) Any member who through change of
employment standing or other circumstances no longer meets the criteria for the
position to which the member was appointed shall no longer be eligible to serve
in that position, and the position on the commission shall become vacant 60
days following the member's change in circumstances. [1965 c.535 s.2; 1973
c.270 s.11; 1975 c.278 s.4; 1979 c.307 s.4]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.360 Members; qualifications.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) The
membership of the Teacher Standards and Practices Commission shall consist of:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (a) Four elementary teachers;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (b) Four junior or senior high school
teachers;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (c) One elementary school administrator;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (d) One junior or senior high school
administrator;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (e) One superintendent of city schools;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (f) One county superintendent or a superintendent
employed by an education service district board;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (g) One member from the faculty of an
approved private teacher education institution in Oregon;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (h) One member from the faculty of a state
institution of higher education;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (i) One member who is also a member of a
district school board; and</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (j) Two members of the general public.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) Except for those members appointed under
subsection (1)(i) and (j) of this section, members must have been actively
engaged in teaching, supervising or administering in the public schools or in
approved teacher education institutions in Oregon for the period of five years
immediately preceding appointment. Acting as an elected representative of
teachers, supervisors or administrators shall be considered teaching, supervising
or administering for the purposes of the five-year experience requirement. In
addition, members appointed under subsection (1)(a) to (f) of this section must
hold valid Oregon teaching or administrative licenses other than restricted
teaching or administrative licenses.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (3)(a) Throughout the term for which
appointed, one of the members appointed under subsection (1)(a) to (j) of this
section must hold a teaching license with an indorsement in some aspect of
special education or have demonstrated knowledge or experience in special
education.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (b) As used in this subsection, “special
education” means specially designed education to meet the goals of the
individual education program of a child with disabilities including regular
classroom instruction, instruction in physical education, home instruction,
related services and instruction in hospitals, institutions and special
schools. [1965 c.535 s.3; 1973 c.270 s.12; 1975 c.278 s.5; 1979 c.307 s.5; 1987
c.503 s.9; 1989 c.244 s.1; 1993 c.45 s.171]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.370</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [1965 c.535 s.5; 1975 c.278
s.6; repealed by 1979 c.307 s.8]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.380 Organization.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) The
Teacher Standards and Practices Commission shall select one of its members as
chairperson, and another as vice chairperson, for such terms and with such
powers and duties necessary for the performance of the functions of such
offices as the commission shall determine.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) A majority of the commission constitutes
a quorum for the transaction of business. [1965 c.535 s.6]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.390 Meetings; expenses.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) The Teacher
Standards and Practices Commission shall meet at least once every six months at
a place, day and hour determined by the commission. The commission shall also
meet at such other times and places as are specified by the call of the
chairperson or of a majority of the members of the commission.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) A member of the commission who is
employed at a public school or by a private teacher education institution or by
a state institution of higher education shall receive no compensation for
services as a member; but subject to any other applicable law regulating travel
and other expenses for state officers, the member shall receive actual and
necessary travel and other expenses incurred in the performance of official
duties as provided by ORS 292.495 (2).</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (3) A member of the commission who serves on
the commission in the capacity of a district school board member or as a member
of the general public shall be entitled to compensation and expenses as
provided in ORS 292.495 (1) and (2). [1965 c.535 ss.7, 8; 1991 c.662 s.4; 1993
c.45 s.172]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.400 Licensing requirements for
out-of-state applicants; reciprocal agreements.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) Except
as provided in subsection (4) of this section, the Teacher Standards and
Practices Commission shall not issue a license to an out-of-state applicant
unless the applicant has met the professional requirements established by rule
by the commission and has completed a course of study substantially similar to
that required for an in-state applicant.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) Notwithstanding subsection (1) of this
section, if the commission establishes that the position or positions to be
filled are in a geographic or subject matter area in which there are an
insufficient number of in-state applicants, the commission may issue a license
to an out-of-state applicant who has completed a course of study approved by
the commission.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (3) In situations described in subsection
(2) of this section, the commission shall adopt by rule standards providing for
equal treatment for graduates of approved Oregon colleges and universities.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (4) Notwithstanding subsection (1) of this
section, the commission may enter into a reciprocal agreement with the
appropriate official of any other state for licensure of applicants from the
state if the commission determines that the standards and requirements for
certification or licensure in that state are substantially similar to the
standards and requirements for licensure under applicable statutes of this
state and rules of the commission.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (5) Teachers granted licenses under
subsections (2), (3) and (4) of this section shall be required to meet all
standards required of Oregon teachers, including the requirements of ORS
342.123, not later than three years following the date of initial granting of
the license. [1965 c.535 s.9; 1973 c.270 s.13; 1979 c.307 s.6; 1981 c.663 s.5;
1987 c.503 s.8; 1993 c.45 s.173; 1993 c.333 s.1]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.410 Executive director; employees.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> The Teacher
Standards and Practices Commission shall appoint a qualified person as
executive director and may, subject to the State Personnel Relations Law,
employ persons to provide such service as the commission shall require. [1965
c.535 s.12; 1973 c.270 s.14; 1997 c.165 s.4]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.420 Member's salary; reimbursement to
district.</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) Membership on the Teacher Standards and Practices
Commission shall not affect a member's compensation from the employer of the
member or any other benefits to which the member is entitled.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) A school district required to employ a
substitute for a teacher or administrator who is absent from employment while
performing duties as a member of the Teacher Standards and Practices Commission
shall be entitled to reimbursement for the district's actual expenses in
employing the substitute. Reimbursement for the expense of employing such
substitutes shall be made by the commission from the Teacher Standards and
Practices Commission Account. [1965 c.535 s.13]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.430 Teacher Standards and Practices
Commission Account; use.</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'> On or before the 10th day of each month, the Teacher
Standards and Practices Commission shall pay into the State Treasury all moneys
received under this chapter during the preceding calendar month. The State
Treasurer shall credit the moneys to the Teacher Standards and Practices
Commission Account. The moneys in the Teacher Standards and Practices
Commission Account are continuously appropriated to the commission for the
purpose of paying its administrative expenses. [1965 c.535 s.15; 1967 c.637
s.8; 1973 c.270 s.15; 1993 c.45 s.174]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>MINORITY TEACHER ACT</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.433 Definitions for ORS 342.433 to
342.449.</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:
-.15pt'> As used in ORS 342.433 to 342.449 and 351.077:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (1) “Minority” means a person who is:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (a) A person having origins in any of the
Black racial groups of Africa but who is not Hispanic;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (b) A person of Hispanic culture or origin;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (c) A person having origins in any of the
original peoples of the Far East, Southeast Asia, the Indian subcontinent or
the Pacific Islands; or</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (d) An American Indian or Alaskan Native
having origins in any of the original peoples of North America.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) “Teacher” includes a teacher or an
administrator. [1991 c.434 s.6; 1993 c.45 s.175]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.435</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [1977 c.635 s.8; repealed by
1981 c.469 s.6]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.437 Goals.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> The State of
Oregon is committed to ethnic-racial equity and, therefore, it is the goal of
the state that by the year 2001 the number of minority teachers, including
administrators, employed by school districts and education service districts
shall be approximately proportionate to the number of minority children enrolled
in the public schools of this state. [1991 c.434 s.2]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.440</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [1971 c.755 s.2; repealed by
1973 c.536 s.39]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.443 Reports to legislature; comparative
data; data collection.</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) The Education and Workforce Policy Advisor shall
report biennially to the Legislative Assembly longitudinal data on the number
and percentage of:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (a) Minority students enrolled in community
colleges;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (b) Minority students applying for admission
to public four-year institutions of higher education;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (c) Minority students accepted in public
four-year institutions of higher education;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (d) Minority students graduated from public
four-year institutions of higher education;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (e) Minority candidates seeking to enter
public teacher education programs in this state;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (f) Minority candidates admitted to public
teacher education programs;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (g) Minority candidates who have completed
approved public teacher education programs;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (h) Minority candidates receiving Oregon
teaching licenses based on preparation in this state and preparation in other
states;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (i) Minority teachers who are newly employed
in the public schools in this state; and</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (j) Minority teachers already employed in
the public schools.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) The advisor also shall report
comparisons of minorities' and nonminorities' scores on basic skills, pedagogy
and subject matter tests.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (3) The State System of Higher Education,
the Department of Education, the Teacher Standards and Practices Commission,
community colleges and school districts shall cooperate with the advisor in
collecting data and preparing the report. [1991 c.434 s.3; 1997 c.652 s.30]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.445</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [1977 c.635 s.9; renumbered
342.485]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.447 Plans for recruitment, admission,
retention and graduation of minority teachers.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) The
State Board of Higher Education shall require each public teacher education
program in this state to prepare a plan with specific goals, strategies and
deadlines for the recruitment, admission, retention and graduation of minority
teachers.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) The state board shall review the plans
for the adequacy and feasibility of the plans and, after making necessary
revisions, shall adopt the plans.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (3) The state board shall adopt rules
governing:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (a) The contents of the plans;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (b) The state board's initial and biennial
review process, including timetables for revising plans; and</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (c) Other matters necessary for carrying out
the provisions of ORS 342.433 to 342.449 and 351.077. [1991 c.434 s.4]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.449 Short title.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> ORS 342.433
to 342.449 and 351.077 shall be known and may be cited as the Minority Teacher
Act of 1991. [1991 c.434 s.1]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.450</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [1965 c.390 s.1; 1969 c.647
s.1; repealed by 1973 c.536 s.39]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>SCHOOL NURSES</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.455 Definition of “school nurse.”</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> “School
nurse” as used in ORS 342.465 and 342.475, means a registered nurse who is
certified by the Teacher Standards and Practices Commission as qualified to
conduct and coordinate the health services programs of a school. [Formerly
678.505]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.460</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [1965 c.390 ss.2, 3; 1969 c.647
s.2; 1971 c.755 s.3; repealed by 1973 c.536 s.39]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.465 Rules; notice if action taken on
license.</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:
-.15pt'> (1) The Teacher Standards and Practices Commission shall adopt by rule
standards necessary for the issuance, denial, continuation, renewal, lapse or
reinstatement of certificates issued under ORS 342.475 (1) to (3) and for
establishment and collection of fees for certification as a school nurse. The
commission may adopt by rule procedures for revocation of a certificate issued
under ORS 342.475 (1) to (3) that are consistent with ORS 342.175 to 342.190.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) The Oregon State Board of Nursing shall
notify the commission whenever the board takes any action on a license issued
under ORS chapter 678 which might affect the ability of the license holder to
practice as a school nurse. [Formerly 678.525; 1993 c.45 s.176]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.470</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [1965 c.390 s.4; 1969 c.647
s.3; 1971 c.755 s.4; repealed by 1973 c.536 s.39]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.475 School nurses; certificates.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) “School
nurse” is established as a category of specialization in nursing.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) The Teacher Standards and Practices Commission
shall issue a certificate as a school nurse to a person who complies with the
rules established by the commission for the certification and practice of
school nursing or who has been certified by the Oregon State Board of Nursing
as a school nurse practitioner. In establishing rules for the certification and
practice of any specialization of school nursing, the commission shall consider
the recommendations of the Oregon State Board of Nursing.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (3) The commission may issue an emergency
certificate that authorizes a person licensed as a registered nurse in this
state who does not meet the requirements of subsection (2) of this section to
practice as a school nurse. Such certificates shall be issued for a limited
time as set by the commission.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (4) Notwithstanding subsections (1) to (3)
of this section, the commission shall issue a certificate in a school nurse
specialization category to a registered nurse who applies for certification and
who is employed by a school, school district or education service district to
conduct and coordinate a school or district health services program or who
serves in such a capacity on a voluntary basis on November 1, 1981. A
certificate issued under this subsection shall be issued without further proof
of qualification by the applicant.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (5) A certificate issued under this section
is not a teaching license. The nurse holding a certificate issued under this
section is not subject to ORS 238.280 or 342.805 to 342.937. [Formerly 678.515]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.480</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [1971 c.755 s.5; repealed by
1973 c.536 s.39]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.485 Commission to consult with and
advise Oregon State Board of Nursing on school nursing.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> The Teacher
Standards and Practices Commission shall consult with and advise the Oregon
State Board of Nursing on the qualifications and practices involved in school
nursing. [Formerly 342.445]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.495 Holder of school nurse certificate
qualified to conduct and coordinate health services program.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) The
holder of a school nurse certificate issued under ORS 342.475 (1) to (3) is
qualified to accept employment to conduct and coordinate the health services
programs of any public school in the State of Oregon. A person licensed as a
registered nurse may use the term “nurse” as part of a title when employed by a
school.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) No school or school district is required
to employ as a nurse a person certified under ORS 342.475 (1) to (3). [Formerly
342.982]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.505</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [Amended by 1955 c.219 s.1;
1961 c.383 s.1; 1965 c.100 s.367; repealed by 1993 c.45 s.177]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

