<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF EMPLOYMENT OF SCHOOL PERSONNEL</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.608 Working hours for licensed
personnel; duty-free lunch period required; exception.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) School
boards shall fix the working hours for full-time and part-time licensed staff
members. They shall direct that full-time staff members be provided a time for
a 30-minute continuous duty-free lunch period during the regularly scheduled
lunch hours.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) Any school principal who fails to
schedule a continuous 30-minute duty-free lunch period in accordance with this
section shall be guilty of neglect of duty under ORS 342.865.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (3) No teacher shall by oral orders or
written agreement fail to receive a 30-minute lunch period.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (4) School boards shall not be required to
employ special personnel to supervise students during lunch periods.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (5) This section does not apply in school
buildings where fewer than three teachers are employed. [1971 c.201 s.1]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.609</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [1977 c.137 s.1; renumbered
336.081 in 1993]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.610 Minimum salary for substitute
teachers.</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) For the biennium beginning July 1, 1995, teachers
employed as substitute teachers shall not be paid less per day than 80 percent
of 1/190th of the salary of a beginning teacher who holds a bachelor's degree.
For bienniums beginning on and after July 1, 1997, teachers employed as
substitute teachers shall not be paid less per day than 85 percent of 1/190th
of the salary of a beginning teacher who holds a bachelor's degree. The salary
of the substitute teacher shall be computed as required in this subsection
based on the statewide average salary for beginning teachers who hold
bachelor's degrees. The Department of Education shall compute the statewide average
salary to be used for purposes of this subsection, using the latest data
available to the department, but not data from earlier than the preceding
school year.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) The school district shall set the
working hours for a substitute teacher, and, when employed, shall pay the
substitute teacher a salary which is no less than one-half of the daily minimum
salary as computed under subsection (1) of this section. However, if the
substitute teacher is employed for more than one-half day, the substitute teacher
shall receive a full day's pay.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (3)(a) Notwithstanding subsection (1) of
this section, teachers employed as substitute teachers for more than 10
consecutive days in any one assignment for the same teacher shall not be paid
after the 10th day of the assignment less per day than 100 percent of 1/190th
of the statewide average salary computed in subsection (1) of this section for
districts with no salary scale; or, for districts with a salary scale, 1/190th
of the employing school district's salary for a beginning teacher who holds a
bachelor's degree.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (b) Used sick leave, whether paid or unpaid,
and weekends, school holidays and days when schools are closed by weather or
other conditions and when substitute teachers are not required to appear in
person at the school shall not be considered in determining consecutive days
for purposes of this subsection.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (c) When substituting for a part-time
teacher, the part of the day worked by the substitute shall count as a full day
in determining consecutive days for purposes of this subsection.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (4) Subsections (1) to (3) of this section
do not apply to substitute teachers represented in a bargaining unit in the
school district by which they are employed. [Amended by 1955 c.130 s.1; 1957
c.262 c.1; 1965 c.100 s.377; 1967 c.625 s.1; 1971 c.536 s.1; 1977 c.531 s.1;
1979 c.167 s.1; 1987 c.402 s.1; 1991 c.198 s.1; 1995 c.793 s.1]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.613 Contracts with teachers for return
of part of salary prohibited.</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'> No district shall enter into a contract with any
teacher whereby the teacher shall return to the district any part of the salary
of the teacher. If any board and teacher enter into such contract, the contract
is void and the teacher's teaching license shall be revoked. [Formerly 342.525;
1967 c.67 s.12]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.615</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [Amended by 1965 c.100 s.386;
repealed by 1979 c.166 s.1]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

