<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.680</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [Repealed by 1965 c.100 s.456]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.685</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> [Repealed by 1965 c.100 s.456]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>SEXUAL HARASSMENT</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.700 Policy on sexual harassment; posting
and availability of policy.</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'> It is the policy of the State of Oregon that sexual
harassment will not be tolerated in schools. A school district shall adopt a
policy on sexual harassment for students and staff that meets the requirements
of ORS 342.704. A school district shall make the sexual harassment policy
available to students, parents of students and staff. A school district's
sexual harassment policy shall be posted on a sign that is at least 8.5 by 11
inches in size. The school district shall post the sign in all grade 6 through
12 schools in the school district. [1997 c.272 s.1]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            Note: </span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'>342.700 to 342.708 were enacted
into law by the Legislative Assembly but were not added to or made a part of
ORS chapter 342 or any series therein by legislative action. See Preface to
Oregon Revised Statutes for further explanation.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.704 Adoption of school district policies
on sexual harassment required; contents.</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> (1) The State Board of
Education shall adopt by rule minimum requirements for school district policies
on sexual harassment of students by staff and other students including, but not
limited to, requirements that:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (a) All staff and students are subject to
the policies;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (b) Sexual harassment of students includes:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (A) A demand for sexual favors in exchange
for benefits; and</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (B) Unwelcome conduct of a sexual nature
that has the purpose or effect of unreasonably interfering with a student's
educational performance or that creates an intimidating, offensive or hostile
educational environment;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (c) All complaints about behavior that may
violate the policy shall be investigated;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (d) The initiation of a complaint in good
faith about behavior that may violate the policy shall not adversely affect the
educational assignments or study environment of the student; and</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (e) The student who initiated the complaint
and the student's parents shall be notified when the investigation is
concluded.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (2) The State Board of Education shall adopt
by rule minimum requirements for school district policies on sexual harassment
of staff by students and other staff including, but not limited to,
requirements that:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (a) All staff and students are subject to
the policies;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (b) Sexual harassment of staff includes:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (A) A demand for sexual favors in exchange
for benefits; and</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (B) Unwelcome conduct of a sexual nature
that has the purpose or effect of unreasonably interfering with a staff
person's ability to perform the job or that creates an intimidating, offensive
or hostile work environment;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (c) All complaints about behavior that may
violate the policy shall be investigated;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (d) The initiation of a complaint in good
faith about behavior that may violate the policy shall not adversely affect any
terms or conditions of employment or work environment of the staff complainant;
and</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            (e) The staff member who initiated the
complaint shall be notified when the investigation is concluded. [1997 c.272
s.2]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            Note: </span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'>See note under 342.700.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'>            342.708 ORS 342.700 and 342.704 not
limitation on or prerequisite for other rights and remedies.</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:-.15pt'> Nothing in
ORS 342.700 and 342.704 is intended to limit or operate as a prerequisite to
pursuing any rights or remedies provided under other statutes or the common
law. [1997 c.272 s.3]</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
line-height:12.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
